title: Class Action Claims Frigidaire Gas Ranges Are Defective, Do Not Heat to Desired Temperature
description: A class action lawsuit claims that certain Frigidaire gas ranges consistently heat 25 to 30 degrees cooler than the oven temperature entered by the user due to a defect.

title: Class Action Claims Princeton University Failed to Safeguard Private Info Against November 2025 Data Breach
description: A class action alleges Princeton University failed to prevent a Nov. 2025 data breach that exposed the personal info of at least 100K people.

title: $400K Planned Parenthood of Montana Settlement Resolves Class Action Over August 2024 Data Breach
description: A $400K Planned Parenthood settlement offers cash and data monitoring services to individuals who may have been impacted by an Aug. 2024 data breach.

title: $1.1M Behavioral Health Resources Settlement Ends Class Action Suit Over November 2024 Data Breach
description: A $1.1M Behavioral Health Resources offers cash and data monitoring services to individuals who may have been impacted by a November 2024 data breach.

title: Generic Cymbalta Settlement Ends Class Action Over Alleged Cancer-Causing Impurities in Duloxetine
description: A Breckenridge Pharmaceutical settlement ends a lawsuit that alleged generic Cymbalta (duloxetine) was contaminated with cancer-causing impurities.

title: $1.72M Navy Federal Credit Union Settlement Ends Lawsuit Over Alleged Electronic Funds Transfer Act Violations
description: A $1.72M Navy Federal Credit Union settlement ends a class action lawsuit that alleged the credit union acted in violation of the Electronic Funds Transfer Act.

title: $4.17M Plainridge Park Casino Settlement Ends Class Action Lawsuit Over Rewards Card Monthly Statements
description: A $4.17M settlement ends litigation that alleged Plainridge Park Casino unlawfully failed to provide rewards card members with monthly statements.

title: Contra Costa County Settlement Offers Cash, Credit Monitoring to Resolve Data Breach Class Action
description: Contra Costa County, California, has agreed to settle a class action lawsuit over 2022 data breach.

title: $716K+ Gotham Comedy Club Settlement Resolves Case Over Allegedly Hidden Fees in Online Ticket Sales
description: Gotham Comedy Club has agreed to pay over $716K to settle a class action lawsuit over allegedly hidden fees in online ticket sales.

title: Whoop Lawsuit Claims Blood Pressure Monitors Are Falsely Advertised as ‘Medical-Grade’
description: A class action lawsuit alleges that Whoop blood pressure devices do not offer medical-grade health insights as advertised.

title: $450K Trinity Health Class Action Settlement Ends Lawsuit Over January 2021 Data Breach
description: A $450K Trinity Health settlement offers cash to individuals who may have been impacted by a Jan. 2021 data breach.

title: $7.5M HelloFresh Settlement Ends Litigation Over Automatic Subscription Renewals in California
description: A $7.5M HelloFresh settlement offers cash refunds to California consumers who were enrolled in an automatic subscription without consent.

title: $1.23M+ New York Community Bank Settlement Ends Class Action Over ‘Retry’ Fees for ACH, Check Transactions
description: A $1.23M+ New York Community Bank settlement offers cash to consumers wrongfully charged certain insufficient funds, overdraft and out-of-network ATM fees.
